  "commentary": "With SPX at 6825.12 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6820 (-34.4B) and positive gamma resistance at 6840 (+18.8B), dealers are caught in a critical hedging zone where they're being forced to buy into this 5-point range as they're short gamma. The BREAKOUT regime with -47.5B total GEX means any move above 6840 will trigger dealer selling into strength, while a break below 6820 forces aggressive dealer buying that could amplify downside momentum. Watch 6820 as the key amplification level - below here dealers become major buyers, above 6840 they become sellers.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile whipsaw action between 6820-6840 until one side breaks decisively.",
